channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Google's New Phones Aren't Really About the Phones
item.description: Latest Pixel series is another distribution channel for Google’s premium AI services—plus a bit of a flex against Apple.

item.title: UBS smashes second quarter profit expectations as Credit Suisse consolidation boosts revenue
item.description: Analysts expected revenue of $11.5 billion, according to an LSEG poll.

item.title: The Big Risk for the Market: Becoming an AI Echo Chamber
item.description: Artificial intelligence was still the main source of profit growth for the S&P 500 this earnings season. But AI-driven firms are largely boosting each other’s profits.

item.title: UBS CEO says it's too early to talk about a U.S. recession, but a slowdown is possible
item.description: UBS CEO Sergio Ermotti said market volatility could intensify in the second half of the year, but he does not believe the U.S. is heading into a recession.

item.title: Mars Nears Roughly $30 Billion Deal for Cheez-It and Eggo Maker Kellanova
item.description: The acquisition would push Mars, known for M&M’s and Skittles, into supermarkets’ chips and cracker aisles.

item.title: Chinese tech giant Tencent's quarterly profit jumps 82% as key gaming unit accelerates
item.description: Tencent shares are up 27% this year, in part due to excitement around a new game called Dungeon & Fighter Mobile (DnF Mobile).

item.title: The Dramatic Turnaround in Millennials' Finances
item.description: It wasn’t the avocado toast. Soaring home prices and smart investments have helped change the narrative for a generation once mocked for being perpetually behind.

item.title: World's largest sovereign wealth fund posts $138 billion in first-half profit as AI demand boosts tech
item.description: Norway's massive sovereign wealth fund on Wednesday posted first-half profit of 1.48 trillion kroner ($138 billion).

item.title: Commonwealth Bank of Australia's Profit Falls Amid Competition
item.description: Australia’s biggest bank said its annual net profit fell 6%, with growth in its core businesses offset by ongoing competition.

item.title: Home Depot expects sales to weaken as consumers grow more cautious
item.description: Home Depot's CFO said homeowners are now deferring projects due to a "sense of greater uncertainty in the economy."
